event.title: Keane
event.description:
KEANE, one of Britain’s best loved bands, return to Australia for a run of April show dates to highlight their undeniable collection of perfectly crafted stellar pop.

With over 8 million album sales worldwide and a bundle of awards spanning Brits to Ivor Novellos, KEANE are fresh from a sold-out UK arena shows but looking forward to a playing more intimate venues in the first shows here in 5 years.

Introducing themselves to the world at large via the 2004 ‘HOPES & FEARS’ album, KEANE continued to surprise with 2006’s ‘UNDER THE SEA’, which songs including ‘Somewhere Only We Know’, ‘Crystal Ball’, ‘Everybody’s Changing’ & ‘Is It Any Wonder’. 2008 saw the release of the band’s 3rd album ‘PERFECT SYMMETRY’, a thrillingly bold album cementing Rice-Oxley’s position as one of the finest British songwriters to emerge this decade.

Don’t miss this technicolour explosion of pure, unashamed pop energy - audible in every finger-clicking and life-affirming chorus.

event.title: Keane
event.description:
"Our eyes are already misting over at news that British sentimentalists Keane will return to our shores in April. It’s been five years since the band’s last visit, and they’ll be coming straight from a stadium-filling circuit of the UK.

2008 heralded Keane’s third album, Perfect Symmetry, which sold zillions of copies and no doubt powered a few TV drama crescendos. They’ll play relatively close-quarters shows in Perth, Sydney, Melbourne and Brisbane – speedy sell-outs are a given. "

event.title: Estrella Levante SOS4.8
event.description:
Vuelve el Festival Estrella Levante SOS 4.8

Los días 1 y 2 de mayo de 2009 el festival Estrella Levante SOS 4.8 abrirá de nuevo la temporada de festivales de verano, con 48h non-stop al ritmo de la mejor música de vanguardia nacional e internacional.

Estrella Levante SOS 4.8 es un festival con pretensiones diferentes, y el primero en nuestro país que se articula de acuerdo a tres pilares fundamentales: Música, Arte contemporáneo y Voces, un espacio para la Reflexión.

El año pasado más de 26.000 personas bailaron al ritmo de The Chemical Brothers, Rufus Wainwright, James o Fangoria entre otros. La edición de 2009 repite con el sonido de la mejor música de vanguardia y aumenta su oferta musical con dos nuevos escenarios, que en total dotan al festival de cuatro espacios.

La sección de Arte Contemporáneo liderada por Jota Castro, Comisario Artístico, mostrará los trabajos de Michelangelo Pistoletto, Amy Prince, Mark Leckey (Premio Turner 2008), International Festival, David Ellis o Fernando Bryce.
Jota Castro es un artista franco-peruano afincado en Bruselas, evocador del humor trivial y el sarcasmo políticamente incorrecto, y aborda en su trabajo distintos problemas sociales reinterpretando hechos conectados con la actualidad y sus experiencias personales.

VOCES, el espacio para la reflexión, unirá este año a un espectro más amplio de profesionales. Artistas, intelectuales, economistas, sociólogos y filósofos se darán cita en las mesas redondas abiertas a la participación ciudadana, bajo el lema ¿Y ahora qué?

Si quieres saber más sobre Festival Estrella Levante SOS 4.8 suscríbete a nuestra newsletter y recibirás todas las novedades relacionadas con el festival, las confirmaciones de cartel y mucho más…

event.title: Oxegen

artists.artist: Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds

event.description:
Oxegen is an annual music festival, held since 2004, sponsored by Heineken International. It was previously called Witnness, which ran from the year 2000 and was sponsored by Guinness. Oxegen was originally a two-day festival but for 2008 will be expanded to three days. It takes place at the Punchestown Racecourse in County Kildare, Republic of Ireland and has an average attendance of around 80,000 a day, with around half of these camping on site for the duration, and the rest travelling to the site each day. The festival is promoted by MCD.

While Oxegen has not yet reached the iconic status of Glastonbury, it still manages to attract a large quantity of high profile acts each year. Generally, the festival’s line-up is identical to that of T in the Park, which runs on the same weekend, but in Scotland. Many acts play Oxegen on the day that they’re not playing TitP.
As well as six stages of music, there are four large areas for camping which are subdivided by colour. Stalls and shops are also provided, as well as toilet and shower areas. The toilet facilities have been improved upon in recent years and are now adequate for the large number of people at the festival. There is also a funfair adjacent to the arena, featuring a big wheel and other rides, such as the “Magic Carpet”, the “Big Drop”, and the roller coaster.
